data.value: Katso idea
T‰ysin yhden ihmisen kokemus ilman ryhm‰painetta

Kertos‰e:
En tahtonut tapella, tahdo erota,
en kuvitellut koskaan t‰n loppuvan,
en tahtonut sua rikkoo, tehd‰ meille n‰in mut vaik
kuinka rakastaakin toinen toistaan j‰lleen satuttaa


S‰e 1:
Anteeks kulta ett‰ en oo v‰h‰‰n aikaan soittanut
ollaan oltuu kiireisii ja tyˆst‰ oon vain toipunut
Mul on ik‰v‰ ja haluisin sut t‰nne,
makaamaan rannal kun yll‰ loistaa t‰hdet
Mietin ett‰ olisit l‰mmin mun syliss‰
vannoin pysyy mukanas yl‰  ja ala m‰iss‰,
Silti aika kuluu pois mut vieden
suudelmat sun on en‰‰ muistois mielen
Niinku se kosketuksen mielikuva, kun
suutelen sua ja me yhes keinutaan
ku ilta tummuu, ja kuulen vain sut
kuu loistaa suhun ja hikeen kastut
Kai molemmat yritti liian v‰h‰n koska
tultiin t‰h‰n eik‰ tarpeeks n‰h‰
Kohta viel‰ palaan taas, tule rakas vastaan
Ollaan viel‰ viisaampii et voidaan taas rakastaa


S‰e 2:
Tuntu niinku tarvitsin  jonkun toisen
nimes unohtuu ja muihin nimiin sen sotken
Kun m‰ viimeks l‰hin ovet paukkuen
tuli vastaan nainen uutta toivoo huokuen
M‰ torjuin iloiset tunteet  mut meid‰n
katseet kun kohtas katos murheet
Miten tunteen sammutan?  En tii‰, mutta
otteeseen mut se saa,  en kiell‰
M‰ pelk‰‰n sit‰ taas  et ihastun
tai et rakastun ja petyn enk‰ palaudu
En haluu rakastuu toiseen joka heti j‰tt‰‰
aika on arvokasta kahestaan viett‰‰
Enk‰ haluu yksin‰‰n tunnevuoristorataan,
mut sen kyll‰ kest‰‰ kun on joku jolle jakaa
En sulle tunnusta, ett‰ oot mun ainoa,
jos s‰ tahot niin, huomaat olevas mun vaimona


Bridge:
V‰lil sanoin et mua kaduttaa, tahdoin riidat unohtaa,
mut ne s‰ilyy ain sun sis‰ll‰, vaik m‰ en huomaiskaan
M‰ n‰ytt‰nyt en tarpeeksi, kuinka paljon v‰litin
Voin m‰ olla taas nyt mukava, mit‰ sill‰ korjaisin

Chorus:
I didn't want to fight, I don't want to break up,
i never imagined this would end
I didn't mean to break you, to do this to us, but...
no matter how one loves the other, one hurts the other again


Verse 1a:
Sorry honey I haven't called in a while
I've been busy and I've just recovered from work
I miss you and I want you here
to lie down on the beach when there are only stars above

Verse 1b:
I dream how you would be warm in my arms
I promised to stay with you through the ups and downs
Still, time passes by taking me away
your kisses are memories in my mind now

Verse 1c:
Like that vision of us touching
in wich I kiss you and we rock together
when the night gets dark, and the only thing I hear is you
the moon shines on you and you are drenched in sweat

Verse 1d:
I guess neither of us tried enough
because we came here and don't see enough of each other
I'll be back in a moment, come meet me wife
Let's be a little wiser so that we can love again


Verse 2a:
I feel like I need someone else
I forget your name and I mess it up with another name
When I left with slamming doors last time,
a woman came up with an air of hope

Verse 2b:
I rejected the happy feelings,
but when our eyes met, the sorrows disappeared
How to turn off the feeling? I don't know
but sometimes it gets me, I won't deny

Verse 2c:
I'm afraid that I'll fall in love again
or that I fall in love, and fail and never recover
I don't want to fall in love with someone who immediately leaves
time is precious to spend alone with someone

Verse 2d:
And I don't want to ride the emotional roller coaster alone anymore,
but you can handle it when you share everything
I won't confess to you that you are my only one,
if you want, you will realize that you are my wife


Bridge:
Sometimes I said I was sorry, I wanted to forget the fights,
but they remain inside me, even if I don't notice it
I didn't show enough how much I cared
I can be nice to you again now, what would I fix with its

Maksimoi itsem‰‰r‰‰misoikeuden ja valinnanvapauden
Ihmiset vain toistavat huonoja piirteit‰‰n, eiv‰tk‰ voi asialle mit‰‰n
'Satutamme toisiamme aina uudestaan' on melko rankaisevaa
Asenne on melko hyv‰ksyv‰ kaikkia ihmisten huonoja piirteit‰ kohtaan
'katkeransuloisuutta, jossa henkilˆ saa helpotusta kielteisist‰ asioista' kuvastaa kertos‰ett‰. Toisaalta s‰keet on melko iloisia v‰lill‰.
Pohditaan vakavissaan omia tunnemyrskyj‰ ja mit‰ asialle voisi tehd‰
Kevyet asiat sanotaan merkityksellisesti ja kohtalomaisesti, joten melko dramaattinen yleiss‰vy.
Kertos‰e on melko toivoton: 'satutamme toisiamme aina uudestaan'. Toisaalta, s‰e on melko toiveikas.
Asioista n‰hd‰‰n huonot puolet, etenkin kertsiss‰: 'mut ne s‰ilyy ain sun sis‰ll‰'.
Avoin uusille parisuhteille ja seikkailuille
Uuden kumppanin tapaaminen on todella herkk‰‰. Myˆs tappelu on herkk‰‰ normaaliin n‰hden.
Puhutaan vaimosta ja siit‰ ett‰ on vain yksi parisuhde kerrallaan.
Koko kappaleen er‰s m‰‰rite on normaali heteroseksuaalinen parisuhde.
Kappalessa haetaan kauneutta normaaleilla parisuhdesymboleilla, jotka eiv‰t ole kuitenkaan liian kliseisi‰, kuten rakastelua hiekkarannalla.
Sallitaan miehen muuttuminen parisuhteessa ja ajautuminen omalle tielleen

Verse 2a:
I felt like I needed someone else
I was forgetting your name, and messing it up with another
When I did leave, slammed the door
And this woman came with air of hope

Verse 2b:
First, I rejected the happy feelings
But when our eyes met, sorrows disappear
I didn't know how to turn off the feelings
I accepted them, won't deny

Verse 2c:
I'm scared of falling in love
And I'm scared of failing and not recovering
Context of time is precious
when spending with someone

I don't want to ride on the emotional roller coaster alone
it's easier when you have someone to share it with
I don't confess that you're my only one

I want to forget our fights
Our fights remain inside me
Though you don't notice

I haven't shown
how much I care

Chorus:
I didn't want to fight, don't want to part ways,
I never imagined it would turn out this way,
I didn't want to break you, do this to us,
No matter how much we love each other, we still hurt each other in the end.

Verse 1:
Sorry my love, I haven't been calling,
We both have had our share of busy days and trying to recover,
I miss you and I'd wish you were here,
Lying on the beach with stars as our ceiling,
I thought I could keep you warm in my embrace,
Promised to stay with you through the good and bad days,
Still time passed and all we have are the memories of our kisses,
Just the thought of us dancing together as the evening falls,
I can only hear you, with the moon light shining over you and me,
We both tried too little in our relationship,
Not seeing it coming, the chances of us being together are fading,
Soon I'll be coming back, come and meet me,
Let's be smarter and fall in love again.

Verse 2:
It felt like I need someone else,
Forgetting the name and filling it with someone else instead,
When I last left, the door swinging behind me,
I saw a woman full of new hope,
I rejected those happy feelings but when our eyes met, the worries faded away,
How do I turn those feelings off? I don't know but it still feels right,
I'm still scared of being taken away again,
If I fall in love and in the end I just break again,
I don't want to fall in love only to be left,
Time was precious when we were together,
I won't admit that you are my only one,
If you want it, soon you'll be my wife.

Bridge:
Sometimes I said that I regret it, wanting to forget the fight,
But they will remain buried in you, even if I don't notice it,
I didn't show enough love, what can I fix now?
Can I be nice again, what can I do with it?

Chorus:
I don't wanna battle, I just want a truce
I thought this would all be more than news
I'm sorry for hurting you, it wasn't my plan,
There's too many miles to get where love began

Verse 1:
My apologies for the late response,
I'm coming down off from this awful stress
What I wouldn't give to just be with you,
Laying out on that beach with just the stars on view
Dreaming of the way you feel in my arms,
I swore that we'd make it through, through these highs and lows
Mama time started busin' by,
All your kisses become memories stuck in my mind
I remember that vision of us embracing,
Kissing softly while we just swayed
As the night got darker, the only sound I heard was you,
The moonlight on you, and how your sweat drenchin' through
Guess we just ain't trying hard enough,
We get to a point, when peepin' lasts so much
I'll be back for sure, meet me there soon,
Let's be smarter now, so for love we can resume

Verse 2:
I felt I had to find someone else,
Your name I forget, and another I just rushed
Slamming doors, I left last time,
The presence of a woman that brought a hope on to last
Feelings I dismissed when I saw her,
But when we locked eyes, all that sorrow was through
Don't know how to end the feeling,
Sometimes it overtakes, can't deny it is real
Afraid I would get in love and fail,
Fall, never recover, so never begin I'd favor
Don't want to fall in love with someone discharge,
Taking time precious to get to be with someone
And I'm no longer ready for that roller coaster ride,
But with you we'll get through, for we share everything inside
Not confessing to you that you are my one,
You'll soon realize that you are my number one

Bridge:
I said I'm sorry a thousand times,
These fights, they only stay in mind
But I haven't shown you how much I love,
So we can now start all again and repair what needs be done.

1. What Steve Packard (born 2013, likes Pop-Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Initial reaction and critically important and negative things in lyrics only:
-I don't want to fight and I don't want to break up. That's not how relationships should be. It seems like it's too late to repair the damage done, but if the damage caused by us still hurts one another, then things have to change for the better.

2. What Mila Smith (born 2009, likes KoreaPop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It's really sad to hear that one of them is always hurting the other in the end. Relationships don't have to end this way. There is always hope and something to work for. We just have to be positive and put in the effort.

3. What Paul Lee (born 2003, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- Sounds like someone is stuck in a cycle of pain and dissatisfaction. It's understandable that they want to try to make things work but it's important to make sure both sides are equally invested in the relationship. That way, both can benefit from it. 

4. What Tina Smith (born 1996, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is really heartbreaking. It's hard to maintain a relationship when one of you is always doing something to hurt the other. Relationships should be built on trust and understanding, not pain and disappointment.

5. What Bobby Reynolds (born 1995, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It sounds like the couple in the song have been through a lot and they are struggling to find the balance between being together and going their separate ways. It's hard to make a relationship work but if you both believe in it, it can definitely be done. 

6. What Rachel Johnson (born 1992, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is a tough situation to be in. It's hard to find the balance between staying in a relationship and leaving it. Both participants have to be willing to put in the effort for it to work. It's about having patience and understanding.

7. What Shawn Johnson (born 1991, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- You have to want to stay together. If it isn't worth the effort anymore, then it's time to move on. Relationships should be healthy and both partners should be willing to make it work. No one should be hurting each other in the process.

8. What Jake White (born 1989, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It saddens me to hear that even when they love each other, there always seems to be hurt in the end. Relationships should bring joy and happiness, not more heartache. People should strive to bring positive energy into a relationship.

9. What Cyrus McCall (born 1988, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It sounds like the couple in the song is stuck in an endless cycle of love and pain. It's hard to repair a relationship when one of you is always hurting the other. It's important to put in the effort to make the relationship work as best as you can. 

10. What Kelly Taylor (born 1987, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- This is a really difficult situation to be in. Love can be so complicated and can hurt so much. It's important to be honest with yourself and the other person in order to make a relationship work.

11. What Mike Richards (born 1977, likes Metal) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics:
- It's heartbreaking to see someone in such a delicate and painful situation. Relationships don't have to end up this way. It takes courage to hope for and stay in a relationship, and both parties have to be willing to work together and repair the hurts.

suggestion.content:
Missin' you, thinkin' 'bout the way it used to be,
With soft sand on shore, and a sky of midnight blue.

Longin' for you, strugglin' to find a remedy,
Under starlit night, here I stay in misery.

Squeezin' through, yearnin' for the way we used to be,
Out on this beach with sacred heavens above me.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
I'm longin' for you, can't find a way to break free,
Lying in the sand, night sky as far as I can see.

Thinkin' 'bout you, livin' with this agony,
Gazing up at stars as I lie here on the sea.

Beggin' for you, strugglin' to keep my sanity,
Somethin' 'bout the stars and waves that brings tranquility.

Missin' you, achin' for a different destiny,
Staring up at stars while da sand runs under me.

Longin' so deep, searchin' for a way to break free,
Out here on the beach, skies above full of majesty.

Cravin' for you, longin' for a different life,
Dark night glows bright, washin' away all this strife.

Desperately reachin' out, wishin' for a way to be,
Prayin' to the moon, stars shinin' down on me.

Achin' for you, searchin' for a way to make it right,
Underneath the stars, here my soul starts to take flight.

Needing you, desirin' to make a stand for me,
Out here on this beach, under night's scenery.

Hoping you can, missin' your touch and company,
Stranded on the shore, lookin' at stars so heavenly.

Mournin' for you, cravin' for a chance to be,
Lying on the beach, surrounded by the stars' shining glee.

Wishin' for you, desirin' for the way things could be,
Stargazing far away, layin' here so peacefully.

Longin' for you, hopin' to find serenity,
Out here on the beach, skies full of sorcery.

Callin' for you, searchin' for a different way to be,
Feel the sea breeze, stars shinning down on me.

Cravin' for you, wistin' for the way things could be,
Underneath the stars in all the beauty I can see.

parts.name: Verse 1b
source: Dreaming of you, warm in my arms
Promised to stay through up and down
But time passed by,
kisses are memories
Dreaming how you'd be warm in my arms
Promising staying with me through the ups and downs

suggestion.content:
Imagining when I set you free,
To take its course against the grain and destiny.

Reminiscing in those mellow days,
Echoes of soulful joy and sweet summer craze.

Thinking what to blind me most,
Colors lively as a groovin' song would boast.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
Hoping that our love will last,
Flames hot as lyrics with our rhymes blast.

Dreaming of how my heart was warmed,
Unconditional love that overcame all storms.

Wondering how this could be true,
Perfectly transcribed with stories so true.

Longing just to hold your hand,
Persistent touch that made all dreams stand.

Contemplating all the roads ahead,
Cool breeze whispering future ahead.

Praying to my silent God,
Heart's asylum, where all I need is odd.

Desiring our night would linger,
Shared moments have a rap-like finger.

Fantasizing of the secret hideaway,
Deeper in our hearts, 'tis hidden away.

Speculating how I kept you here,
Flow of a gush of faith despite in fear.

Contriving what seemed to be,
Rhythm of our union made us see.

Yearning for when I had you near,
The anthem of our love so clear and sincere.

Believing that I'd always be,
Fated heart that sang as free.

Hoping for another try,
Music of our passion to defy.

Cherishing the memories we held,
Tunes flowing similar to tales we tell.

Fancying for all the ways we ran,
Doors open to our journey that we both began.

source: Time passing by, taking me away
Kisses now just memories

suggestion.content:
Living life flying, no one can stay
Find me now on the deep blue highway

Visions and dreams become reality
From this false world it's my true entity

Passion and fury delineate me
Lost in the sounds, from the trees I be

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
Turn up the heat, cause I'm on the prowl
In these midnight streets, spit out my howl

Spreading love true and free
Give me everlasting harmony

Life's a journey mountaineering
Always give your heart some steering

Your song will always accompany
My life's soundtrack written in harmony

Distorted sound echoes through the night
Bringing dreams that give me insight

See what you want, believe it or not
Follow the stars, and search the plot

Living with rhymes, stories we tell
Let me jump in, this path my yell

My story is blaring, don't need no more
Lines of my soul, spin on the floor

Rap beats start up, as the night ignites
From darkness it's my heart that sites

Keep it true, this my decree
From these words the boom-bap speaks

Rock and roll keeps me alive
An adrenaline surge never arrives

The energy rises, the world around's swaying
In this revolution I'll be playing

Running away just not me
Let the truth, be the key

My dreams ignite, as the flames grow high
Ashes below, eternal sky

Life's a game, of wondering why
Wanting the truth, I start to fly

parts.name: Verse 1c
source: Memories of us touching
We kissed, we rocked together
When night got dark, I did hear only you
The moon was shining, you were drenched in sweat
Touching, in which I kiss you
and we rock together

suggestion.content:
Gazing, the moment that we share
Singing out together without a care

Dancin' in a state of pure bliss
Going wild, enjoyin' the night like this

Feelin' free like a cosmic blaze
Groovin' ever on enchanted ways

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
Living it up with an old-school joy
Rocking wild in a funk-filled ploy

Lovin' strong in a peaceful mood
A feel-good vibe that will soothe

Troubadour style is poetically true
Laying down rhymes that will stir and move

Singin' out in a bright accord
Harmonies that will reward

Sparked up, under the deep blue ray
hypnotic groove with a magic sway

Breaking out into fierce desire
Won't hold back a moment of fire

Rockin' hard with a mighty rap
Taking down this microphone trap

Rising up to a moody crest
Rythm and soul that will soothe the stress

Heads bop to the hip-hop sound
Real tight rhymes that won't let down

Getting into that activating mode
Abso-positively rhyming in an overload

Singing out with the psychedelic sway
Rockin' hard, through day to day

Taking flight in a magical trance
Making it all into perfect chants

Dancing it up, into a bright light
An embrace of passion that turns it right

Making mellow music with an historic nod
A mix of genre, all down the line on the road

Crooning out a classic brand
Rocking soul to a glitter strand

source: When night gets dark, the only thing I hear,
Is you, moon shining on you drenched in sweat

suggestion.content:
When I'm weak, I feel no fear,
My music guides me, free me from tears.

When strength is lost and I am alone,
I scream out loud, and keep pushin' on.

When sadness comes to me in the night,
Embrace my soul, shines bright the light.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
I'm a hustler, but I'm not scared,
Goin' do what I gotta do, no scared.

When the night grow dark and deep,
My faith shall arise, joy I will keep.

When troubles come it's so hard to take,
Can't win no matter how much I stake.

Love is hard, but I'm not lost,
In the darkness, you are my frost.

When I'm despaired and far from home,
Craving for some peace and roam.

When it's all too much, my heart is torn,
I look for truth, no need to mourn.

All my pain, I can release,
Gunnin' for some answers in this peace.

Out of the darkness, I can hope,
Just one moment, I need to cope.

Night here, it's so cold,
No retreat, I gotta hold.

When night's grow dark and silent,
Pass the mic, keep the vibes terrific.

I'm driven on by my dreams,
Can't be caged, I must be free.

When I fear, I trip and fall,
No breadcrumbs, gotta crawl.

When night calls, no more light,
My dreams keep me alive and bright.

When all around me it's dark,
My heart still shines, a sky so stark.

When night falls, I slow my stride,
Climb the stars, put my faith aside.

parts.name: Verse 1d
source: Maybe we should've tried more,
I will be back in a moment
Let's be wiser so that
we can love again
Not trying enough, being here,
Not seeing enough of each other
I'm being back in a moment, Meeting my wife,
a little wiser able to love again

parts.name: Verse 2a
source: I felt like I needed someone else
I was forgetting your name, and messing it up with another
When I did leave, slammed the door
And this woman came with air of hope
Needing someone else, Forgetting your name,
and messing it up with another name
Leaving last time with slamming doors
A woman coming up with an air of hope

parts.name: Verse 2b
source: First, I rejected the happy feelings
But when our eyes met, sorrows disappear
I didn't know how to turn off the feelings
I accepted them, won't deny
Rejecting happy feelings
When eyes met sorrows disappearing
Not knowing how to turn off the feeling
Sometimes getting me, won't deny

parts.name: Verse 2c
source: I'm scared of falling in love
And I'm scared of failing and not recovering
Context of time is precious
when spending with someone
Afraid falling in love again
And failing and never recovering
With someone who immediately leaves
Time precious, spending alone with someone

parts.name: Verse 2d
source: I don't want to ride on the emotional roller coaster alone
it's easier when you have someone to share it with
I don't confess that you're my only one
Maybe you will realize that you should be my wife
Not wanting to ride emotional roller coaster alone anymore
Being able to handle it when sharing everything
Not confessing to you, being my only one
If you want to realize you are my wife

parts.name: Chorus 1
source: I didn't want to fight, I don't want to break up
I never imagined this could end

parts.name: Chorus 2
source: I didn't mean to break us, do to us like this
We were loving each other, but hurting again

parts.name: Bridge 1a
source: And I say I'm sorry and
I want to forget our fights
Our fights remain inside me
Though you don't notice

parts.name: Bridge 1b
source: I haven't shown
how much I care
I can be nice again,
but what can I fix with it anymore
